# UI Conventions

## Icons

When adding icons, use the **IonIcons** set via **Iconify** (`@iconify/react`).

```tsx
import { Icon } from "@iconify/react";

<Icon icon="ion:heart-outline" aria-hidden />
```

- Use the `ion:` prefix (e.g. `ion:add`, `ion:add-outline`, `ion:close`, `ion:pencil-outline`).
- Prefer outline icons by default; use filled variants on hover/active when matching existing patterns (`HeaderIconLink`, `HeroIconButton`).
- Do not use other Iconify sets (e.g. `mdi:`, `lucide:`, `fa6:`) or ad-hoc SVGs unless the user explicitly requests otherwise.

## Headings and Subheadings

Static UI headings and subheadings use **Title Case**.

Applies to:
- `Heading` components and `h1`–`h6`
- Page hero titles (`PageHero` `title`)
- Modal titles (`AppModal` `title`)
- Table column headers and stat-card labels that act as section titles
- Illustrated-message / section headings

Examples:
- "Add Snack", "Account Settings", "Quick Actions", "Snack Name"
- Articles/prepositions stay lowercase when appropriate: "Create a Wishlist", "Sign In to SnackMates"

Do **not** Title Case user-generated content (wishlist titles, display names, bios, descriptions).

Body text, button labels, and form field labels are sentence case unless they are clearly headings.

## Theme / Appearance

Light/dark mode controls belong **only** in the profile dropdown (`UserMenu` → Appearance section).

- Do **not** add floating `ThemeSwitcher` controls to authenticated app pages (dashboard, messages, wishlists, etc.).
- `ConditionalThemeSwitcher` uses an allowlist of public utility routes only; new `(app)` routes must not be added there.
- If a page renders inside `AppShell`, theme toggles come from the profile menu — nowhere else.
